
[1]version

   VER'SION, n. [L. versio.]

   1. A turning; a change or transformation; as the version of air into
   water. [Unusual.]

   2. Change of direction; as the version of the beams of light.
   [Unusual.]

   3. The act of translating; the rendering of thoughts or ideas expressed
   in one language, into words of like signification in another language.
   How long was Pope engaged in the version of Homer?

   4. Translation; that which is rendered from another language. We have a
   good version of the Scriptures. There is a good version of Pentateuch
   in Samaritan. The Septuagint version of the Old Testament was made for
   the benefit of the Jews in Alexandria.
